======================================================================
PART 3: INCLUSION-EXCLUSION / M√ñBIUS FUNCTION
======================================================================

The OCF says: H(T) = Œ£_Œ© (-1)^{n-comp(Œ©)} where Œ© ranges over
"odd-cycle covers" of T. The 2^k pattern suggests a BINARY choice
at each cycle: include it or not.

For the M√∂bius function on the Boolean lattice of cycle subsets:
  Œº(‚àÖ, S) = (-1)^|S|

And the inclusion-exclusion gives:
  f(S) = Œ£_{U ‚äÜ S} (-1)^{|S|-|U|} g(U)

The formula H = Œ£_S 2^|S| where S ranges over disjoint cycle sets
is equivalent to:
  H = Œ£_S 2^|S| = evaluation of IP at x=2

This is the PARTITION FUNCTION of the hard-core lattice gas at Œª=2.


